H0.text: Which American state has been nicknamed the Equality State because in 1869 it granted voting rights to women as well as men. Utah

H1.text: Which American state has been nicknamed the Equality State because in 1869 it granted voting rights to women as well as men. California

H2.text: Which American state has been nicknamed the Equality State because in 1869 it granted voting rights to women as well as men. Oregon

H3.text: Which American state has been nicknamed the Equality State because in 1869 it granted voting rights to women as well as men. Wyo.

A4.text: Utah granted full voting rights to women in 1870, 26 years before becoming a state.

A5.text: Utah granted women's suffrage in 1870, not 1869.

A6.text: Wyoming granted suffrage to women earlier than Utah.
